title.narrative: BR Municipal APL: Sao Luis Enhancing Municipal Governance and Quality of Life Project

description.narrative: The objective of the São Luís Enhancing Municipal Governance and Quality of Life Project is to improve public service in the Bacanga Basin of São Luís Municipality, and enhance the capacity of the city government in promoting local economic development and municipal management.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.A.1 (a) and (b) | Description :Sao Luis will maintain the UGP throughout implementation untilproject completion, with competent staff in adequate numbers for theduration of the project. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.A.1 (c) | Description :An implementation consulting firm will be hired within three months afterEffectiveness | Due Date :31-Dec-2013
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.B | Description :Sao Luis will ensure that the project is implementated in accordance with theOperations Manual | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.D.1 | Description :Borrower shall carry out the Project in accordance with the provisions andrecommendations of the Safeguards Frameworks | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.D.2 | Description :For civil works involving involuntary resettlement, bidding documents will beissued after Bank's review and approval of the respect ive RAP | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.E.1 | Description :The borrower will enforce the provisions of the Concession Agreement Amendmentwith CAEMA. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, I.E.2 | Description :The borrower will enforce the provisions of the Bacanga Dam Agreement with theState of Maranhao | Frequency :Yearly

title.narrative: Families threatened with flooding from regular tidal movements of the Bacanga Lake in project targeted area be relocated to the satisfaction of residents

actual.value: 18% (108 families voluntarily resettled in the housing units of Pianco VII and VII of an estimated total of 595).

title.narrative: Increases in percent of sewage collected and treated in the targeted area
Bacanga Dam floodgates completely repaired and operated effectively

target.value: Bacanga dam repaired and floodgates properly operated

title.narrative: Development of the local economic development strategy, and budget allocated to undertake main actions from the strategy

baseline.value: Forum of Sustainability Development in Sao Luis

target.value: Main actions from the strategy implemented

actual.value: Activities under the LED strategy were developed: (i) a database with policy and decision making socioeconomic support information;(ii) a capacity building plan for the municipal staff; and (iii) a municipal program for institutional supply and acquisition.

title.narrative: Project targeted areas acquire macro drainage capacity to handle an intense storm every 25 years and micro drainage capacity for a storm every 5 years

actual.value: Capacity improved: Macro drainage works in the Coroado area were completed; macro drainage works in Bicas areas are underway(progress at 99%); rehabilitation of the Bacanga dam not yet conducted.

title.narrative: Development of a competitiveness enhancement plan for one economic cluster, and implementation of recommended short-term actions from the plan by the end of project

target.value: Competitiveness enhancement plan for the tourism cluster developed and short term actions from the plan implemented

actual.value: Competitiveness enhancement plan for the tourism cluster developed and short term actions from the plan implemented.

title.narrative: Integrated water, drainage, sanitation and solid waste plan developed and adopted

actual.value: Integrated Municipal Sanitation Plan (WSS, drainage and solid waste) developed; public consultations held; Plan not yet submittedto approval at the legislative body

title.narrative: Increased consumer satisfaction with water, sanitation, drainage, and urban services

target.value: Survey conducted, and aggregate population satisfaction level improved compared to previous survey

actual.value: One survey conducted (baseline). The procurement process for the intermediate and final surveys faced delays, and were notconducted yet.
